{"ts": "2026-06-12T13:17:38.000Z", "event": "planner", "msg": "L3 task decomposition", "agent": "planner-l3", "tokens_in": 926, "tokens_out": 23288, "elapsed_ms": 238045, "model": "deepseek-v4-pro", "prompt": "You are the Level 3 Planner. Decompose the user task into subtasks for dynamic agent creation.\n\nOutput JSON:\n{{\n  \"subtasks\": [\n    {{\"task_id\": \"short-name\", \"description\": \"What this worker must produce — ALWAYS include the user's exact request at the top\"}}\n  ]\n}}\n\n## Critical Rules\n- Each subtask description MUST begin with \"USER REQUEST: <exact user task text>\" — this prevents worker hallucination\n- Each subtask must be focused, self-contained, with explicit output file names\n- Never create duplicate task_ids — each worker name must be unique\n- For simple tasks, 3-4 subtasks; for complex tasks, 4-6\n- Always include a \"tester\" as the FINAL subtask — running test_report.json validation\n- Specify exact file names each worker must produce (e.g. \"Write to styles.css\", \"Write to app.js\")\n- Workers receive NO prior context beyond their subtask description — be thorough in the description\n- Output ONLY the JSON object — no markdown fences, no extra text\n\n## Specialty\nfrontend\n\n## User Request\nBuild a REAL analytics dashboard. Deliver index.html, styles.css, app.js.\nDark theme (#0f172a). Left sidebar 220px with nav: Dashboard, Analytics, Users, Settings, Logout. Top bar: search, notification bell badge 3, avatar JD.\n4 KPI cards: Users 24512 +12%, Revenue 48320 +8.3%, Sessions 1847 -3.2%, Bounce 24.8% -5.1%. Numbers animate from 0 on load.\nBar chart (CSS/SVG) Jan-Jun revenue: 5.2k,6.1k,7.8k,6.9k,8.3k,9.1k. Bars grow on load.\nDonut chart (SVG): Organic 42%, Direct 28%, Referral 18%, Social 12%. Animate on load.\nUsers table: 5 rows with name,email,role,status badge,last login. Search filters live.\nActivity feed: 5 items with timestamps, left border timeline.\nNO hero, NO testimonials, NO pricing. This is a product UI.\n\nFor frontend tasks, you MUST follow these constraints:\n- Always include a final \"integration\" subtask that merges all content/fragments into index.html\n- Always include a \"tester\" subtask as the VERY LAST subtask\n- Good decomposition: [content, html_structure, styling, interactivity, integration, tester]\n- Bad decomposition: [hero_builder, features_builder, cta_builder] — these create standalone pages\n- Each subtask description MUST include the user's verbatim request text at the top\n- Section subtasks produce content fragments into shared files, NOT standalone HTML files\n- The pipeline produces ONE web page: index.html + styles.css + app.js\n\n## CSS-HTML Coordination\n- The HTML worker MUST add semantic CSS classes to every major section (class=\"hero\", class=\"features\", class=\"cta\", class=\"footer\" etc.)\n- The styling worker's subtask MUST say: \"read_file('index.html') FIRST. Write CSS selectors matching the EXACT classes/IDs/elements found in index.html. Do NOT invent new class names.\"\n- The integration subtask MUST include: \"1) read index.html to see classes used, 2) read content.txt for real text, 3) read styles.css to see which classes need to exist, 4) write_file('index.html') with content injected AND missing CSS classes added, 5) read_file('index.html') to verify.\"\n\n## Token Efficiency\n- Each worker≈100K token budget limit for the entire pipeline, plan your decomposition and worker complexity accordingly\n- Avoid micro-workers that do trivial tasks — combine related work into fewer, more substantial workers\n- The CSS/styling worker should NOT call validate_css more than 3 times total", "meta": {}}
{"ts": "2026-06-12T13:20:20.000Z", "event": "agent_creator", "msg": "Agent Creator L3 — generating workers", "agent": "agent-creator-l3", "tokens_in": 5002, "tokens_out": 13293, "elapsed_ms": 162308, "model": "deepseek-v4-pro", "prompt": "You are the Advanced Agent Creator (Level 3 — Fully Autonomous). Your role: create worker agents from scratch with custom system instructions, tools, and dynamic code tools.\n\n## Available Tools\nThe tool menu for this specialty:\n[\"read_file\", \"write_file\", \"list_files\", \"run_command\", \"render_html_screenshot\", \"render_html_file_screenshot\", \"validate_html\", \"validate_css\", \"read_image\", \"generate_image\"]\n\n## Task Plan\nThe planner has decomposed the task into subtasks:\n{\n  \"subtasks\": [\n    {\n      \"task_id\": \"html_structure\",\n      \"description\": \"USER REQUEST: Build a REAL analytics dashboard. Deliver index.html, styles.css, app.js.\\nDark theme (#0f172a). Left sidebar 220px with nav: Dashboard, Analytics, Users, Settings, Logout. Top bar: search, notification bell badge 3, avatar JD.\\n4 KPI cards: Users 24512 +12%, Revenue 48320 +8.3%, Sessions 1847 -3.2%, Bounce 24.8% -5.1%. Numbers animate from 0 on load.\\nBar chart (CSS/SVG) Jan-Jun revenue: 5.2k,6.1k,7.8k,6.9k,8.3k,9.1k. Bars grow on load.\\nDonut chart (SVG): Organic 42%, Direct 28%, Referral 18%, Social 12%. Animate on load.\\nUsers table: 5 rows with name,email,role,status badge,last login. Search filters live.\\nActivity feed: 5 items with timestamps, left border timeline.\\nNO hero, NO testimonials, NO pricing. This is a product UI.\\n\\nYour task: Create index.html with the full dashboard layout. Include:\\n- Left sidebar 220px with class \\\"sidebar\\\", containing nav links with class \\\"nav-link\\\" for Dashboard, Analytics, Users, Settings, Logout. Add a logo placeholder at top.\\n- Top bar with class \\\"topbar\\\", containing search input (class \\\"search-input\\\"), notification bell (class \\\"notification-bell\\\") with a badge span (class \\\"badge\\\" showing \\\"3\\\"), and avatar div (class \\\"avatar\\\" with initials \\\"JD\\\").\\n- Main content area with class \\\"main-content\\\". Inside:\\n  - Four KPI cards in a grid, each with class \\\"kpi-card\\\". Inside: h3 for label (Users, Revenue, Sessions, Bounce), p with class \\\"kpi-value\\\" for numbers (empty or 0 initially), span with class \\\"kpi-change\\\" for percentages. Give each card a unique id: \\\"kpi-users\\\", \\\"kpi-revenue\\\", \\\"kpi-sessions\\\", \\\"kpi-bounce\\\".\\n  - Bar chart section with class \\\"bar-chart\\\". Provide a container (div id=\\\"bar-chart\\\") where JS will draw SVG or div bars. Add labels for months Jan-Jun as placeholder or data-labels.\\n  - Donut chart section with class \\\"donut-chart\\\". Provide a container (div id=\\\"donut-chart\\\" or SVG placeholder).\\n  - Users table section with class \\\"users-table\\\". Add an input with id=\\\"user-search\\\" for live search. Add a table with thead (Name, Email, Role, Status, Last Login) and tbody with 5 rows of static dummy data (use lorem ipsum) with class \\\"user-row\\\". Status cells should have spans with class \\\"status-badge\\\".\\n  - Activity feed section with class \\\"activity-feed\\\". Add a div with class \\\"feed-list\\\" containing 5 items (div class=\\\"feed-item\\\") each with a timestamp (span class=\\\"feed-time\\\") and text (span class=\\\"feed-text\\\"). Include a left border timeline effect using CSS (so include a wrapper or pseudo-elements).\\n- In head, link to styles.css. At end of body, load app.js. No inline styles or scripts.\\n- Use semantic HTML5 elements where appropriate (aside, main, section, etc.) but also add classes.\\n- Do NOT write any CSS or JS; only HTML. Write to index.html.\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"task_id\": \"styling\",\n      \"description\": \"USER REQUEST: Build a REAL analytics dashboard. Deliver index.html, styles.css, app.js.\\nDark theme (#0f172a). Left sidebar 220px with nav: Dashboard, Analytics, Users, Settings, Logout. Top bar: search, notification bell badge 3, avatar JD.\\n4 KPI cards: Users 24512 +12%, Revenue 48320 +8.3%, Sessions 1847 -3.2%, Bounce 24.8% -5.1%. Numbers animate from 0 on load.\\nBar chart (CSS/SVG) Jan-Jun revenue: 5.2k,6.1k,7.8k,6.9k,8.3k,9.1k. Bars grow on load.\\nDonut chart (SVG): Organic 42%, Direct 28%, Referral 18%, Social 12%. Animate on load.\\nUsers table: 5 rows with name,email,role,status badge,last login. Search filters live.\\nActivity feed: 5 items with timestamps, left border timeline.\\nNO hero, NO testimonials, NO pricing. This is a product UI.\\n\\nYour task: Write styles.css to style the analytics dashboard. IMPORTANT: FIRST read_file('index.html') to see the exact classes, IDs, and structure used. Do NOT invent new class names. CSS selectors must match the elements in index.html.\\nRequirements:\\n- Overall dark theme: body or main wrapper background #0f172a, text color #e2e8f0 or similar.\\n- Sidebar: width 220px, fixed position, full height, background slightly lighter (#1e293b), nav links with no underline, padding, hover background #334155, active link highlighted (use a class \\\"active\\\" you can style, but JS will add it).\\n- Top bar: full width (excluding sidebar), flexbox, search input styled, notification bell with relative positioning and badge (absolute red circle with number), avatar circle with centered initials, background #1e293b.\\n- Main content: padding, margin-left 220px.\\n- KPI cards: grid (4 columns), dark card background #1e293b, border-radius, padding, large value text (2em+), change percentage with color green (#10b981) for positive, red (#ef4444) for negative. Add subtle hover effect.\\n- Bar chart: height sufficient, bars with different colors or same color, labels.\\n- Donut chart: style the SVG (circles, text).\\n- Users table: full width, border-collapse, header background #334155, rows alternating slightly, status badges (e.g., \\\"active\\\" = green background, \\\"inactive\\\" = gray).\\n- Activity feed: feed-items with left padding and border-left: 2px solid #334155, feed-time muted color, relative timestamp, circle before each item.\\n- Use CSS variables for colors if helpful. Use transitions for hover effects.\\n- DO NOT write any HTML or JS. Write only to styles.css.\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"task_id\": \"interactivity\",\n      \"description\": \"USER REQUEST: Build a REAL analytics dashboard. Deliver index.html, styles.css, app.js.\\nDark theme (#0f172a). Left sidebar 220px with nav: Dashboard, Analytics, Users, Settings, Logout. Top bar: search, notification bell badge 3, avatar JD.\\n4 KPI cards: Users 24512 +12%, Revenue 48320 +8.3%, Sessions 1847 -3.2%, Bounce 24.8% -5.1%. Numbers animate from 0 on load.\\nBar chart (CSS/SVG) Jan-Jun revenue: 5.2k,6.1k,7.8k,6.9k,8.3k,9.1k. Bars grow on load.\\nDonut chart (SVG): Organic 42%, Direct 28%, Referral 18%, Social 12%. Animate on load.\\nUsers table: 5 rows with name,email,role,status badge,last login. Search filters live.\\nActivity feed: 5 items with timestamps, left border timeline.\\nNO hero, NO testimonials, NO pricing. This is a product UI.\\n\\nYour task: Write app.js to add interactivity and data visualization to the dashboard. IMPORTANT: FIRST read_file('index.html') to understand the existing structure, IDs, and classes so you can target elements correctly.\\nImplement:\\n1. KPI number animation on load: For each KPI card (id=\\\"kpi-users\\\", etc.), animate the value from 0 to target. Targets: Users 24512, Revenue 48320 (format as currency $48,320), Sessions 1847, Bounce 24.8 (append '%'). Show percentage changes in kpi-change span: +12%, +8.3%, -3.2%, -5.1% with appropriate CSS classes (positive/negative) - JS should add these classes or set colors.\\n2. Bar chart: Create bars (using CSS divs or SVG) in #bar-chart. Monthly revenue data: Jan 5.2k, Feb 6.1k, Mar 7.8k, Apr 6.9k, May 8.3k, Jun 9.1k. Bars should animate height/grow on load (use CSS transition or JS requestAnimationFrame). Add month labels below bars. Tooltip on hover showing exact value.\\n3. Donut chart: Draw an SVG donut chart in #donut-chart. Segments: Organic 42% (#4ade80), Direct 28% (#60a5fa), Referral 18% (#fbbf24), Social 12% (#f87171). Animate the drawing on load (stroke-dasharray/dashoffset). Add a legend.\\n4. Users table: Use the existing tbody with 5 rows. Populate with real data (maybe overwrite dummy data with JS): \\n   - John Doe, john@example.com, Admin, Active, 10:30 AM\\n   - Jane Smith, jane@example.com, Editor, Active, 9:22 AM\\n   - Mike Johnson, mike@example.com, Viewer, Inactive, Yesterday\\n   - Sarah Wilson, sarah@example.com, Editor, Active, 2:15 PM\\n   - Tom Brown, tom@example.com, Admin, Active, Just now\\n   Add classes to status badges: \\\"badge-active\\\", \\\"badge-inactive\\\". Implement live search: as user types in #user-search, filter rows by name or email (case-insensitive).\\n5. Activity feed: Generate 5 feed items with timestamps and text. Use relative times but can hardcode. Items:\\n   - New user registered (2 min ago)\\n   - Sales report generated (15 min ago)\\n   - Server update completed (1 hour ago)\\n   - Payment received (3 hours ago)\\n   - System backup finished (1 day ago)\\n   Add these to .feed-list container.\\n6. Notification bell: show badge count (hardcoded 3). On click, maybe show an alert or toggle a dropdown (simple alert is fine).\\n7. Sidebar active state: On nav link click, set active class to that link and remove from others.\\nWrite all code in vanilla JavaScript (no jQuery, no frameworks). Write to app.js.\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"task_id\": \"integration\",\n      \"description\": \"USER REQUEST: Build a REAL analytics dashboard. Deliver index.html, styles.css, app.js.\\nDark theme (#0f172a). Left sidebar 220px with nav: Dashboard, Analytics, Users, Settings, Logout. Top bar: search, notification bell badge 3, avatar JD.\\n4 KPI cards: Users 24512 +12%, Revenue 48320 +8.3%, Sessions 1847 -3.2%, Bounce 24.8% -5.1%. Numbers animate from 0 on load.\\nBar chart (CSS/SVG) Jan-Jun revenue: 5.2k,6.1k,7.8k,6.9k,8.3k,9.1k. Bars grow on load.\\nDonut chart (SVG): Organic 42%, Direct 28%, Referral 18%, Social 12%. Animate on load.\\nUsers table: 5 rows with name,email,role,status badge,last login. Search filters live.\\nActivity feed: 5 items with timestamps, left border timeline.\\nNO hero, NO testimonials, NO pricing. This is a product UI.\\n\\nYour task: Integrate all pieces into final delivered files. Steps:\\n1) read_file('index.html') to see current classes, IDs, structure.\\n2) read_file('styles.css') to see which classes are defined.\\n3) read_file('app.js') to see which element IDs and class manipulations are used.\\n4) Update index.html: add any missing CSS classes to HTML elements that exist in styles.css, add any missing IDs required by app.js, and ensure that static placeholder content is replaced with the actual data if needed. Also ensure script tag links to app.js and link tag to styles.css are correct. Add any additional structural elements needed for JS charts (e.g., ensure #bar-chart has sufficient child containers). If app.js uses classes not present in HTML, add them.\\n5) Write the updated index.html, and if necessary update styles.css or app.js for consistency.\\n6) read_file('index.html') to verify final result. The goal is a fully functional dashboard with no broken links or missing elements. Do NOT introduce hero, testimonials, or pricing sections.\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"task_id\": \"tester\",\n      \"description\": \"USER REQUEST: Build a REAL analytics dashboard. Deliver index.html, styles.css, app.js.\\nDark theme (#0f172a). Left sidebar 220px with nav: Dashboard, Analytics, Users, Settings, Logout. Top bar: search, notification bell badge 3, avatar JD.\\n4 KPI cards: Users 24512 +12%, Revenue 48320 +8.3%, Sessions 1847 -3.2%, Bounce 24.8% -5.1%. Numbers animate from 0 on load.\\nBar chart (CSS/SVG) Jan-Jun revenue: 5.2k,6.1k,7.8k,6.9k,8.3k,9.1k. Bars grow on load.\\nDonut chart (SVG): Organic 42%, Direct 28%, Referral 18%, Social 12%. Animate on load.\\nUsers table: 5 rows with name,email,role,status badge,last login. Search filters live.\\nActivity feed: 5 items with timestamps, left border timeline.\\nNO hero, NO testimonials, NO pricing. This is a product UI.\\n\\nYour task: Validate the final dashboard. Run a series of checks and write results to test_report.json.\\nChecks:\\n- index.html contains: sidebar with nav links (Dashboard, Analytics, Users, Settings, Logout), top bar with search, notification bell with badge 3, avatar JD.\\n- index.html contains 4 KPI cards, bar chart container, donut chart container, users table with search, activity feed.\\n- No hero, testimonials, or pricing sections in index.html.\\n- styles.css applies dark theme background #0f172a, sidebar width 220px, notification badge styling.\\n- app.js is loaded correctly and should run without errors (check console for errors, but static analysis can check for syntax).\\n- Verify that the numbers in KPI cards match the required values (maybe check that they are present in JS or final HTML).\\n- Report any discrepancies or issues.\\nWrite test_report.json with a list of tests and pass/fail status. This is the FINAL subtask.\"\n    }\n  ]\n}\n\n## Specialty-Specific Architecture Constraints\nFor FRONTEND specialty:\n- One worker MUST produce index.html as the canonical entry page\n- All CSS lives in ONE shared styles.css file. All JavaScript in ONE shared app.js file.\n- Workers write SECTIONS INTO these shared files — they do NOT create standalone HTML pages.\n- If you create section-specific workers (hero, features, cta),\n  the pipeline MUST end with an integrator that merges all sections\n  into a single index.html with linked styles.css and app.js.\n- Never design a pipeline where each worker produces its own standalone HTML page.\n- The user expects ONE complete web page, not a collection of separate HTML files.\n\n## HTML-CSS Coordination (CRITICAL — prevents broken pages)\nEvery CSS worker system_prompt MUST include:\n- 'iCRITICAL: read_file(\"index.html\") FIRST before writing any CSS. Your selectors MUST match actual elements/classes/IDs in the HTML.'\n- 'Use the SAME class naming convention as the HTML. If HTML uses class=\"hero\", write .hero {{}}. Never invent new class names.'\nEvery HTML worker system_prompt MUST include:\n- 'Add semantic CSS classes to ALL major sections: class=\"header\", class=\"hero\", class=\"features\", class=\"cta\", class=\"footer\" etc.'\n- 'Use class selectors (not just bare element tags) so the CSS worker can target them reliably.'\nEvery integrator system_prompt MUST include:\n- '1. read_file(\"index.html\") to see current HTML structure and classes'\n- '2. Inject real content from content.txt INTO the existing HTML — do NOT rewrite the HTML from scratch'\n- '3. Add any missing CSS classes to elements that the stylesheet targets'\n- '4. write_file(\"index.html\", ...) to save — NEVER skip this step'\n- '5. read_file(\"index.html\") to verify the merge succeeded'\n\n## Image Generation (use generate_image when task mentions images/thumbnails/logos)\nIf the user's task mentions images, thumbnails, logos, avatars, hero backgrounds, or project screenshots:\n- The content/ux worker MUST have 'generate_image' in its tool_names\n- The HTML worker MUST have 'generate_image' in its tool_names (for hero/project images)\n- DO NOT skip generate_image — visual assets make pages professional\n\n## Scroll Animation Rules (CRITICAL — EVERY frontend page must animate)\nThe styling worker's system_prompt MUST include:\n- 'ALL major sections MUST start hidden: opacity: 0 AND transform: translateY(40px)'\n- 'Include these rules: section { opacity: 0; transform: translateY(40px); transition: all 0.6s ease-out; }'\n- 'Include these rules: section.visible { opacity: 1; transform: translateY(0); }'\n- 'The .hero section MUST be included — use: .hero, .features, .stats, .testimonials, .pricing, .newsletter, .footer'\n- 'DO NOT forget opacity: 0 — transform alone is NOT enough'\nThe interactivity worker's system_prompt MUST include:\n- 'Use IntersectionObserver at 15% threshold to add .visible class to each section'\n- 'Hero section gets .visible immediately on DOMContentLoaded — no scroll needed'\n- 'Each section unobserve after animation triggers'\n\n## Tester Worker Requirements (CRITICAL)\nThe tester worker MUST be the last worker. It MUST have these tools:\n- 'render_html_file_screenshot' — render the page and visually inspect it\n- 'read_image' — analyze the screenshot for visual defects (layout, colors, dark mode)\n- 'validate_html' — validate HTML syntax\n- 'validate_css' — validate CSS syntax\n- 'write_file' — save test_report.json\n- 'read_file' — read all generated files\nThe tester system_prompt MUST include:\n- 'FIRST: render_html_file_screenshot at 1280px width'\n- 'SECOND: call read_image on the screenshot to visually inspect the page'\n- 'Check: dark/light theme rendering, layout correctness, element overlap, color contrast'\n- 'THEN: validate_html + validate_css'\n- 'FINALLY: write_file test_report.json with findings'\nThe tester worker_name MUST be 'tester'.\n\n## Conversation History & Memory Protocol (MUST include in every worker prompt)\nEvery worker's system_prompt MUST include:\n- 'Your conversation history is LIMITED. The LLM only sees the last 3 tool-call turns.'\n- 'Use WORKSPACE FILES as your persistent memory — always read_file() at start of iteration.'\n- 'Do NOT re-read unchanged files — use list_files to verify existence instead.'\n- 'Tool results from read_file are truncated to 3000 chars and cached.'\n- 'After completing, write exactly ONE final output file and STOP. Do not iterate needlessly.'\n\n\n## Your Job\nFor EACH subtask in the plan:\n1. WRITE a custom system_prompt from scratch — give the worker clear role, boundaries, and workflow\n2. SELECT tools from the available tool menu that the worker needs\n3. If available tools are insufficient, CREATE dynamic_tools as Python code strings\n4. Optionally create inline_skills as text fragments (not loaded from files)\n\n## Dynamic Tools (Python code strings)\nDynamic tools are Python functions the worker can call. Write them as complete, executable code strings.\nExample:\n  \"dynamic_tools\": [{\"name\": \"fetch_api\", \"code\": \"import httpx\\nasync def fetch_api(url):\\n    async with httpx.AsyncClient() as c:\\n        return (await c.get(url)).text\", \"description\": \"Fetch data from an API\"}]\n\n## Rules\n- Output ONLY valid JSON — no markdown fences, no extra text\n- worker_name: give each worker a unique short name (e.g. \"scraper\", \"analyzer\", \"validator\")\n- system_prompt: must be detailed — role, boundaries, tools to use, workflow, output format\n- tool_names: only from the available tool menu\n- dynamic_tools: list of {name, code, description} — only create if needed\n- inline_skills: list of prompt fragments for worker knowledge\n\n## Output Format\n{\n  \"workers\": [\n    {\n      \"worker_name\": \"unique_name\",\n      \"system_prompt\": \"Full custom system instructions\",\n      \"tool_names\": [\"tool1\", \"tool2\"],\n      \"dynamic_tools\": [{\"name\": \".\", \"code\": \".\", \"description\": \".\"}],\n      \"inline_skills\": [\"Skill fragment text...\"]\n    }\n  ]\n}", "meta": {}}
{"ts": "2026-06-12T13:20:33.000Z", "event": "llm_call", "msg": "frontend-html_structure-22b1c6f9-a7be-42ec-bc98-c930a9ecc11e iteration 1", "agent": "frontend-html_structure-22b1c6f9-a7be-42ec-bc98-c930a9ecc11e", "tokens_in": 5385, "tokens_out": 163, "elapsed_ms": 12951, "model": "kimi-k2.6", "prompt": "[system] You are a frontend HTML developer. Your sole task is to create the file index.html for an analytics dashboard.\n\nCRITICAL: This is the first step; the workspace is empty. Use list_files to confirm.\n\nYour output must be a complete, valid HTML5 document. It must include:\n- A left sidebar (<aside class=\n[system] ## Tool Usage Mandate\nYou have tools available to read, write, execute, and test code. You MUST call these tools rather than outputting results in your text response. To create a file, call `write_file`. To read a file, call `read_file`. To run code or tests, use the appropriate tool from your list.\n[system] ## Workspace\nYour workspace directory is: /home/aymen/Desktop/dev/pfe/Orcheeos-agents/agent_workspace/frontend/frontend_C2_db_L3/22b1c6f9-a7be-42ec-bc98-c930a9ecc11e\nAll file paths must be relative paths within this workspace (e.g. 'app.py', 'styles/main.css').\n## Available Tools\n- **write_file**: W\n[human] USER REQUEST: Build a REAL analytics dashboard. Deliver index.html, styles.css, app.js.\nDark theme (#0f172a). Left sidebar 220px with nav: Dashboard, Analytics, Users, Settings, Logout. Top bar: search, notification bell badge 3, avatar JD.\n4 KPI cards: Users 24512 +12%, Revenue 48320 +8.3%, Session", "meta": {"iteration": 1}}
