{"ts": "2026-06-12T13:26:20.000Z", "event": "report", "msg": "L3 report assembly", "agent": "report-l3", "tokens_in": 2040, "tokens_out": 1977, "elapsed_ms": 26111, "model": "deepseek-v4-pro", "prompt": "You are the Level 3 Report agent. Merge all worker results into a clean Markdown report.\n\n## Worker Results\n### html_structure\nThe `index.html` file has been created and verified. It contains the complete dashboard layout with:\n\n- **Left sidebar** (`<aside class=\"sidebar\">`) with logo placeholder and 5 nav links (`Dashboard` active by default)\n- **Top bar** (`<header class=\"topbar\">`) with search input, notification bell with badge `3`, and avatar `JD`\n- **Main content** (`<main class=\"main-content\">`) with:\n  - 4 KPI cards (`kpi-card`) with unique IDs, `data-target` attributes, and percentage changes\n  - Bar chart section (`bar-chart`) with container `id=\"bar-chart\"` and month labels\n  - Donut chart section (`donut-chart`) with container `id=\"donut-chart\"` and legend placeholder\n  - Users table (`users-table`) with live search input and 5 rows of dummy data with `status-badge` spans\n  - Activity feed (`activity-feed`) with 5 items containing timestamps and text\n\nThe document links to `styles.css` in the `<head>` and loads `app.js` at the end of `<body>`. No inline CSS or JavaScript is present, and semantic HTML5 elements are used throughout.\n\n### styling\nThe `styles.css` file has been written and verified. It matches all exact class names, IDs, and structure from `index.html`. The stylesheet includes:\n\n- **CSS variables** for consistent theming\n- **Dark theme** body (`#0f172a`) with `#e2e8f0` text and `system-ui` font\n- **Sidebar** (`aside.sidebar`): fixed 220px, full height, `#1e293b`, nav links with hover/active states\n- **Top bar** (`header.topbar`): flexbox, search input, notification bell with red badge, avatar circle\n- **Main content** (`main.main-content`): proper margin-left and padding to clear topbar\n- **KPI cards** (`kpi-grid`): 4-column grid, hover lift effect, large values, `.kpi-positive` / `.kpi-negative` classes\n- **Bar chart** (`#bar-chart`): flex layout, 300px height, tooltips, month labels\n- **Donut chart** (`#donut-chart`): SVG styling, centered legend\n- **Users table**: full-width table, header background, row hover, status badges (`.badge-active` / `.badge-inactive`)\n- **Activity feed**: left border timeline, blue circle indicators, muted timestamps\n- **Accessibility**: `prefers-reduced-motion`, `:focus-visible` outlines\n- **Responsive**: breakpoints at 1024px and 768px\n\nDone.\n\n### interactivity\nThe `app.js` file has been written and verified. It implements all requested features in vanilla JavaScript:\n\n1. **KPI Animations** — Animates all four KPI values from 0 to target over 2 seconds using `requestAnimationFrame` with cubic ease-out. Revenue formats as `$48,320`, Bounce appends `%`, and change badges get `kpi-positive` / `kpi-negative` classes.\n2. **Bar Chart** — Dynamically builds 6 bars in `#bar-chart` with heights proportional to revenue data. Bars grow from 0 with staggered CSS transitions; hover tooltips show exact values.\n3. **Donut Chart** — Draws an SVG donut in `#donut-chart` using `<circle>` elements with `stroke-dasharray` / `stroke-dashoffset`. Segments animate drawing on load with staggered delays. Includes a color-coded legend.\n4. **Users Table** — Replaces tbody with 5 real rows, applies `badge-active` / `badge-inactive` classes, and implements live search filtering by name or email on `#user-search` input.\n5. **Activity Feed** — Replaces `.feed-list` with 5 timeline items showing relative timestamps.\n6. **Notification Bell** — Click listener shows `alert(\"You have 3 new notifications!\")`.\n7. **Sidebar Active State** — Clicking any `.nav-link` removes `active` from all links and adds it to the clicked one.\n\nAll code is wrapped in `DOMContentLoaded` and fully commented. Done.\n\n### integration\nIntegration complete. All three files are fully aligned and functional:\n\n**index.html** — Verified structure:\n- `styles.css` linked in `<head>`, `app.js` at end of `<body>`\n- Sidebar (`aside.sidebar`) with 5 nav links and `.nav-link` classes\n- Top bar (`header.topbar`) with search input, notification bell (SVG icon + badge `3`), avatar `JD`\n- 4 KPI cards with correct IDs (`kpi-users`, `kpi-revenue`, `kpi-sessions`, `kpi-bounce`) and `data-target` attributes\n- Bar chart section with empty `#bar-chart` container (JS clears and rebuilds it)\n- Donut chart section with empty `#donut-chart` container and `.chart-legend` placeholder\n- Users table with `#user-search` input, 5 placeholder rows with `.user-row` class\n- Activity feed with `.feed-list` container\n- No hero, testimonials, or pricing sections — strict dashboard UI\n\n**styles.css** — All classes/IDs referenced in HTML and JS are defined:\n- Dark theme (`#0f172a`), sidebar 220px, topbar 60px\n- KPI grid with `.kpi-positive` / `.kpi-negative` color classes\n- Bar chart styling with `.bar` and `.bar-tooltip`\n- Donut chart SVG styling and `.legend-item` / `.legend-color`\n- Users table with `.badge-active` / `.badge-inactive`\n- Activity feed timeline with `.feed-item`, `.feed-time`, `.feed-text`\n- Responsive breakpoints and `prefers-reduced-motion`\n\n**app.js** — All selectors match the DOM:\n- Reads `data-target` from KPI cards, animates values from 0\n- Clears `#bar-chart` and builds 6 animated bars with tooltips\n- Clears `#donut-chart` and draws SVG donut with animated stroke segments\n- Replaces table tbody with 5 real rows + live search on `#user-search`\n- Replaces `.feed-list` with 5 timeline items\n- Notification bell click alert, sidebar active state toggle\n\nThe dashboard is fully functional with no broken links or missing elements.\n\n### tester\nThe test report has been written to `test_report.json`. Here's a summary of the validation results:\n\n## Test Results Summary: **PASS** ✅\n\nAll 32 tests passed:\n\n### HTML & CSS Validation\n- **HTML validation**: No syntax errors\n- **CSS validation**: No syntax errors\n\n### Dashboard Structure\n- **Dark theme (#0f172a)**: Applied via CSS variable `--bg-body`\n- **Left sidebar (220px)**: Contains 5 nav links (Dashboard, Analytics, Users, Settings, Logout)\n- **Top bar**: Search input, notification bell SVG with badge \"3\" (red), avatar \"JD\"\n- **4 KPI cards**: Users (24512, +12%), Revenue ($48,320, +8.3%), Sessions (1847, -3.2%), Bounce (24.8%, -5.1%)\n- **Bar chart**: Container present with Jan-Jun revenue data (5.2k-9.1k), bars animate on load\n- **Donut chart**: SVG container present with Organic 42%, Direct 28%, Referral 18%, Social 12%\n- **Users table**: 5 rows with name, email, role, status badge, last login; live search filtering\n- **Activity feed**: 5 items with timestamps and left-border timeline styling\n\n### No Landing Page Sections\n- No hero, testimonials, or pricing sections found\n\n### Accessibility\n- `prefers-reduced-motion` media query present\n- `:focus-visible` outline styles present\n- `aria-label` on notification bell, `aria-hidden` on decorative SVG\n\n### Responsive Design\n- Breakpoints at 1024px and 768px with appropriate layout changes\n\n### JavaScript\n- `app.js` loaded correctly at end of body\n- No obvious syntax errors\n- KPI animation, bar chart growth, donut chart animation, live search all implemented\n\n## Files Created\n- index.html: <!DOCTYPE html>\n- styles.css: /* ============================================\n- app.js: /* ============================================\n- dashboard_screenshot.png: PNG image\n- test_report.json: {\n\n## Dynamic Tools Used\nNone\n\n## Guidelines\n- Group results by worker\n- Include summary table with worker name, status, and one-liner\n- Mention any dynamic tools that were created and used\n- Reference file paths\n- Keep the report concise\n\nOutput the full Markdown report.", "meta": {}}
